00:00:49.439 --> 00:00:57.759
Also, if you put a question in the Zoom chat and you want me to read it out loud instead of

00:00:57.759 --> 00:01:03.040
calling on you, you could also put a little star at the end of it, and I'll know to just read that

00:01:03.040 --> 00:01:09.519
out loud. But just wanted to make a quick note that the session will be recorded and shared up

00:01:09.519 --> 00:01:16.320
to YouTube as well for anybody who missed it. But with that, I'm so excited to be joined by my

00:01:16.320 --> 00:01:23.279
co-host for today, Nate Kratzer, who is data science manager at Brown Forman. And Nate, I'd

00:01:23.279 --> 00:01:27.680
love to just have you introduce yourself and maybe share a little bit about the work that you do on

00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:34.320
your team today. Great. Thanks, Rachel. And thanks to everyone for being here. Looking forward to

00:01:34.879 --> 00:01:39.919
getting to talk to all of you for this lunch hour, or at least lunch hour where I'm located. Some of

00:01:39.919 --> 00:01:46.320
you may be joining from other time zones. So I'm Nate. I'm a data science manager at Brown Forman.

00:01:47.040 --> 00:01:52.480
Brown Forman is the company that owns Jack Daniels, Woodford Reserve, and several other

00:01:52.480 --> 00:01:59.839
liquor and spirits brands. So I work with two different teams. One of them is a team that

